cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.HC 

This paper is about a chatbot developed using deep reinforcement learning, which involves natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of neural networks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The evaluation of the system through A/B testing with real-world users indicates a focus on human-computer interaction, which could place it in cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the use of crowdsourced data and real-world user interactions suggests a possible connection to cs.SD (Software Engineering).
